{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879042056,"sessionID":"ses_2855dd4b1ffeqb6215FEQBMdF3","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa3af0c001gW6j9gvJzEmTCz","messageID":"msg_d7aa3a25c001a0jvPM28Brmlzm","sessionID":"ses_2855dd4b1ffeqb6215FEQBMdF3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a8c4153eb2c14d889a53b520","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036: Dify 插件集成 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Dify plugin integration in the AgentCube `integrations` module.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-036\n10: - **Module**: `integrations`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Reference Sources**: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Files to Add\n18: \n19: | Path | Description | Type |\n20: |------|-------------|------|\n21: | `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` | Plugin entry point executing `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` | New |\n22: | `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify | New |\n23: | `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry | New |\n24: | `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` implementation | New |\n25: | `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema | New |\n26: | `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` implementation | New |\n27: | `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` dependency pins | New |\n28: | `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md` | Plugin usage guide | New |\n29: | `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md` | Plugin documentation | New |\n30: | `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md` | Plugin privacy policy | New |\n31: | `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` | Dify ignore file | New |\n32: | `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png` | Plugin icon (light) | New |\n33: | `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png` | Plugin icon (dark) | New |\n34: | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app with agents and sandbox runner | New |\n35: | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | FastAPI and LangChain dependencies | New |\n36: | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Container image definition | New |\n37: | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment manifest | New |\n38: | `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | Analyzer documentation | New |\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## Files to Modify\n43: \n44: | Path | Description | Change Type |\n45: |------|-------------|-------------|\n46: | | | |\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Files to Delete\n51: \n52: | Path | Description |\n53: |------|-------------|\n54: | | |\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Requirements\n59: \n60: ### AR-036-001: Dify Plugin Package Structure\n61: \n62: The system SHALL provide a complete Dify plugin package with all required files for plugin discovery and execution.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: AR-036-001-A — Plugin package contains required files\n65: \n66: - **GIVEN** the plugin package root directory at `integrations/dify-plugin/`\n67: - **WHEN** the directory is inspected for file presence\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, and optional documentation files (`GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore`)\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: AR-036-001-B — Plugin entry point executes framework runner\n71: \n72: - **GIVEN** `main.py` is defined as the plugin entry point\n73: - **WHEN** the plugin process starts via the manifest-declared entrypoint\n74: - **THEN** `main.py` SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ### AR-036-002: Plugin Manifest Structure\n79: \n80: The system SHALL provide a `manifest.yaml` with all required Dify plugin metadata.\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-036-002-A — Manifest contains required fields\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** a valid `manifest.yaml` file\n85: - **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n86: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include:\n87:   - `version`: `\"0.0.2\"`\n88:   - `type`: `\"plugin\"`\n89:   - `author`: `\"volcano-sh\"`\n90:   - `name`: `\"agentcube\"`\n91:   - `label`: mapping for `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` to `\"Agentcube\"`\n92:   - `description`: multilingual strings for AgentCube description\n93:   - `icon`: `\"icon.png\"`\n94:   - `icon_dark`: `\"icon-dark.png\"`\n95:   - `resource`: subtree with `memory`, `permission` (including `tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n96:   - `plugins.tools`: list containing `provider/agentcube.yaml`\n97:   - `meta`: object with `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n98:   - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: AR-036-002-B — Tool provider wiring\n101: \n102: - **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references `provider/agentcube.yaml`\n103: - **WHEN** the plugin is loaded by Dify\n104: - **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### AR-036-003: Tool Provider Descriptor\n109: \n110: The system SHALL provide a YAML descriptor for the AgentCube tool provider.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: AR-036-003-A — Provider descriptor structure\n113: \n114: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` exists\n115: - **WHEN** the descriptor is parsed by the integration runtime\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n117:   - `identity`: with `author`, `name`, multilingual `label` and `description`, and `icon`\n118:   - Optional commented `oauth_schema` block\n119:   - `tools`: list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n120:   - `extra.python.source`: `\"provider/agentcube.py\"`\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### AR-036-004: Tool Parameter Schema\n125: \n126: The system SHALL provide a YAML descriptor for the code interpreter tool with complete parameter schema.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: AR-036-004-A — Tool parameter schema definition\n129: \n130: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` exists\n131: - **WHEN** the tool schema is parsed\n132: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n133:   - `identity.name`: `\"agentcube-code-interpreter\"`\n134:   - `identity.author`: `\"agentcube\"`\n135:   - `identity.label` / `description`: human and LLM-oriented strings\n136:   - `parameters`: list including:\n137: \n138: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n139: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n140: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n141: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n142: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: python, javascript, typescript |\n143: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n144: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n145: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n146: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n147: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n148: \n149:   - `extra.python.source`: `\"tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\"`\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### AR-036-005: Provider Implementation\n154: \n155: The system SHALL provide a Python implementation of the tool provider class.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: AR-036-005-A — Provider class structure\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.py` exists\n160: - **WHEN** the module is imported\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` extending `ToolProvider` with a `_validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None` method\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: AR-036-005-B — Provider raises validation error\n164: \n165: - **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` instance with invalid credentials\n166: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition\n167: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: AR-036-005-C — Provider validation passes\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` instance with valid credentials\n172: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` executes without errors\n173: - **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ### AR-036-006: Tool Implementation\n178: \n179: The system SHALL provide a Python implementation of the code interpreter tool.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: AR-036-006-A — Tool class structure\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` exists\n184: - **WHEN** the module is imported\n185: - **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` extending `Tool` with:\n186:   - `_invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]` that calls `execute(**tool_parameters)` and yields `create_json_message(result)`\n187:   - `execute` method accepting parameters: `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language` (default \"python\"), `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse` (default False), and `**kwargs`\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: AR-036-006-B — Tool returns JSON message\n190: \n191: - **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` with valid parameters\n192: - **WHEN** `_invoke` is called by Dify\n193: - **THEN** the tool SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: AR-036-006-C — Tool delegates to SDK client\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n198: - **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n199: - **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK `CodeInterpreterClient` to perform the corresponding remote operations\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ### AR-036-007: Plugin Dependencies\n204: \n205: The system SHALL provide a `requirements.txt` with pinned dependency versions.\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: AR-036-007-A — Dependency file content\n208: \n209: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n210: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n211: - **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ### AR-036-008: PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Application\n216: \n217: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that orchestrates PCAP analysis using AgentCube code interpreters.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: AR-036-008-A — Application startup with API key\n220: \n221: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable\n222: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n223: - **THEN** it SHALL initialize `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, and `REPORTER` agents and bind to `0.0.0.0:8000`\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: AR-036-008-B — Application startup without API key\n226: \n227: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started without a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n228: - **WHEN** the application attempts startup\n229: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail with an error rather than serve requests without credentials\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: AR-036-008-C — Analyze endpoint accepts file upload\n232: \n233: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n234: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with a PCAP file upload (`pcap_file` as `UploadFile`)\n235: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: AR-036-008-D — Analyze endpoint accepts path parameter\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n240: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with `pcap_path` form field (alternative to file upload)\n241: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ### AR-036-009: PCAP Analyzer Configuration\n246: \n247: The system SHALL read configuration from environment variables with appropriate defaults.\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: AR-036-009-A — Default configuration values\n250: \n251: - **GIVEN** the service starts with only `OPENAI_API_KEY` set\n252: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n253: - **THEN** it SHALL use:\n254:   - `OPENAI_API_BASE`: default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`\n255:   - `OPENAI_MODEL`: default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`\n256:   - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`: default `my-interpreter`\n257:   - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`: default `default`\n258:   - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`: default `5`\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: AR-036-009-B — Environment variable overrides\n261: \n262: - **GIVEN** environment variables `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` are set\n263: - **WHEN** the service starts\n264: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided values instead of defaults\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ### AR-036-010: PCAP Analyzer Sandbox Integration\n269: \n270: The system SHALL integrate with AgentCube sandbox via `SandboxRunner`.\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: AR-036-010-A — SandboxRunner initialization\n273: \n274: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is constructed with name, namespace, and warmup_sec\n275: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL be ready to execute commands via `run()`, upload files via `upload_file()` and `upload_bytes()`, and can be stopped via `stop()`\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: AR-036-010-B — File upload to sandbox\n279: \n280: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n281: - **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n282: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: AR-036-010-C — Command execution in sandbox\n285: \n286: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` with an active session\n287: - **WHEN** `run(command)` is invoked\n288: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and return structured execution results\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ### AR-036-011: PCAP Analyzer Container Image\n293: \n294: The system SHALL provide a Dockerfile for building the analyzer container.\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: AR-036-011-A — Dockerfile base and entrypoint\n297: \n298: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` is built\n299: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n300: - **THEN** it SHALL use base image `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`, set `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, expose port `8000`, and run `uv run pcap_analyzer.py`\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: AR-036-011-B — SDK vendoring\n303: \n304: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile build context includes `sdk-python/agentcube/`\n305: - **WHEN** the image is built\n306: - **THEN** it SHALL copy the agentcube SDK into the image at `./agentcube/`\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ### AR-036-012: PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n311: \n312: The system SHALL provide a Kubernetes deployment manifest.\n313: \n314: #### Scenario: AR-036-012-A — Deployment manifest structure\n315: \n316: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n317: - **WHEN** applied to a cluster\n318: - **THEN** it SHALL create a Deployment with:\n319:   - Container image `pcap-analyzer:latest` with `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n320:   - Port `8000` TCP\n321:   - Resource requests: `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`\n322:   - Resource limits: `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n323: \n324: #### Scenario: AR-036-012-B — Environment variable wiring\n325: \n326: - **GIVEN** the deployment is applied\n327: - **WHEN** the pod starts\n328: - **THEN** it SHALL have environment variables:\n329:   - `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`\n330:   - `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: AR-036-012-C — Process launch in cluster\n333: \n334: - **GIVEN** the deployment's container specification\n335: - **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n336: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `[\"uv\"]` with args `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ### AR-036-013: SDK Integration\n341: \n342: The system SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK for code interpreter and agent runtime operations.\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: AR-036-013-A — SDK import in tool\n345: \n346: - **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` is executed\n347: - **WHEN** the tool needs to communicate with AgentCube\n348: - **THEN** it SHALL import and use `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube`\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: AR-036-013-B — SDK import in analyzer\n351: \n352: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` runs analysis\n353: - **WHEN** it needs to execute code in a sandbox\n354: - **THEN** it SHALL import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube.code_interpreter`\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: AR-036-013-C — SDK exception handling\n357: \n358: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n359: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n360: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (from `agentcube.exceptions`) with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ## Acceptance Criteria\n365: \n366: - [ ] AC001: Plugin package contains all required files (main.py, manifest.yaml, provider files, tool files, requirements.txt)\n367: - [ ] AC002: Plugin entry point executes `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n368: - [ ] AC003: manifest.yaml contains all required Dify plugin metadata fields\n369: - [ ] AC004: Provider descriptor (`provider/agentcube.yaml`) contains identity, tools list, and Python source reference\n370: - [ ] AC005: Tool descriptor (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`) contains complete parameter schema\n371: - [ ] AC006: Provider implementation raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on invalid credentials\n372: - [ ] AC007: Tool implementation delegates to `CodeInterpreterClient` and returns JSON messages\n373: - [ ] AC008: requirements.txt pins `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n374: - [ ] AC009: PCAP analyzer validates API key at startup and fails if missing\n375: - [ ] AC010: PCAP analyzer `/analyze` endpoint accepts file upload or path parameter\n376: - [ ] AC011: PCAP analyzer uses default configuration values when env vars are not set\n377: - [ ] AC012: SandboxRunner provides upload_file, upload_bytes, run, and stop methods\n378: - [ ] AC013: Dockerfile uses uv base image, exposes port 8000, runs pcap_analyzer.py\n379: - [ ] AC014: Kubernetes deployment wires secrets and environment variables correctly\n380: - [ ] AC015: SDK exceptions (CommandExecutionError) are properly handled\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## Configuration Changes\n385: \n386: | Key | Old Value | New Value | Description |\n387: |-----|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n388: | | | | |\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## Database Schema Changes\n393: \n394: | Table | Change | SQL |\n395: |-------|--------|-----|\n396: | | | |\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## API Changes\n401: \n402: ### New APIs\n403: \n404: | Method | Path | Description |\n405: |--------|------|-------------|\n406: | POST | `/analyze` | Analyze PCAP file with LLM orchestration |\n407: \n408: ### Modified APIs\n409: \n410: | Method | Path | Description |\n411: |--------|------|-------------|\n412: | | | |\n413: \n414: ### Deprecated APIs\n415: \n416: | Method | Path | Description |\n417: |--------|------|-------------|\n418: | | | |\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ## Architecture Notes\n423: \n424: ### Key Components\n425: \n426: | Component | Path | Description |\n427: |------|------|-------------|\n428: | Plugin Entry | `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` | Dify plugin process entry |\n429: | Plugin Manifest | `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` | Root plugin metadata |\n430: | Provider | `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` | Tool provider implementation |\n431: | Tool | `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | Code interpreter tool |\n432: | PCAP Analyzer | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI application |\n433: | Sandbox Runner | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | AgentCube sandbox integration |\n434: | Deployment | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment |\n435: \n436: ### Environment Variables\n437: \n438: | Variable | Default | Description |\n439: |----------|---------|-------------|\n440: | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | (required) | OpenAI-compatible API key |\n441: | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | API endpoint |\n442: | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | Model name |\n443: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | (required) | AgentCube Workload Manager URL |\n444: | `ROUTER_URL` | (required) | AgentCube Router URL |\n445: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | `my-interpreter` | Code interpreter name |\n446: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | `default` | Kubernetes namespace |\n447: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | Sandbox warmup duration |\n448: \n449: ---\n450: \n451: ## References\n452: \n453: - Base design: `integrations/design.md`\n454: - Base spec: `integrations/spec.md`\n455: - SDK design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n456: - SDK spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n457: - Dify plugin source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`\n458: - PCAP analyzer source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`\n\n(End of file - total 458 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Dify plugin integration in the AgentCube `integrations` module.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-036\n- **Module**: `integrations`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Reference Sources**: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`\n\n---\n\n## Files to Add\n\n| Path | Description | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879042036,"end":1775879042052}}}}
