{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879083905,"sessionID":"ses_2855dd4b1ffeqb6215FEQBMdF3","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa3dbf5001obTH4RPF8DkWZv","messageID":"msg_d7aa3c8230011wjzGO76KtZnNQ","sessionID":"ses_2855dd4b1ffeqb6215FEQBMdF3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_e77cfba50d6d43778bdb217a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成\n\n**Module:** integrations  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Dify Plugin Package Structure\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory structure\n- [ ] **T002** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` with entry point `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n- [ ] **T003** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` with required Dify plugin metadata (version 0.0.2, type plugin, author volcano-sh, name agentcube, labels, icons, resources)\n- [ ] **T004** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` with `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n- [ ] **T005** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` file\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Plugin Icons\n\n- [ ] **T010** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png` (plugin icon light)\n- [ ] **T011** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png` (plugin icon dark)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Tool Provider Descriptor\n\n- [ ] **T020** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml` with identity, tools list, and Python source reference\n- [ ] **T021** Verify provider descriptor contains `identity`, `tools`, and `extra.python.source`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Tool Provider Implementation\n\n- [ ] **T030** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` with `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` class extending `ToolProvider`\n- [ ] **T031** Implement `_validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None` method\n- [ ] **T032** Implement error handling that raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on invalid credentials\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Tool Descriptor\n\n- [ ] **T040** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` with complete parameter schema\n- [ ] **T041** Verify tool schema includes all parameters: router_url, workload_manager_url, language, code, command, session_id, session_reuse, code_interpreter_id\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Tool Implementation\n\n- [ ] **T050** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` with `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` class\n- [ ] **T051** Implement `_invoke` method that yields JSON messages via `create_json_message`\n- [ ] **T052** Implement `execute` method delegating to `CodeInterpreterClient` from agentcube SDK\n- [ ] **T053** Handle SDK exceptions including `CommandExecutionError`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Plugin Documentation\n\n- [ ] **T060** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md` with plugin documentation\n- [ ] **T061** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md` with usage guide\n- [ ] **T062** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md` with privacy policy\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: PCAP Analyzer Application\n\n- [ ] **T070** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory structure\n- [ ] **T071** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` FastAPI application\n- [ ] **T072** Implement startup validation for `OPENAI_API_KEY` (fail if missing)\n- [ ] **T073** Implement `/analyze` endpoint accepting `pcap_file` upload or `pcap_path` parameter\n- [ ] **T074** Configure default values: OPENAI_API_BASE, OPENAI_MODEL, CODEINTERPRETER_NAME, SANDBOX_NAMESPACE, SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\n- [ ] **T075** Implement agent orchestration with PLANNER and REPORTER agents\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9: PCAP Analyzer Dependencies\n\n- [ ] **T080** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` with FastAPI, LangChain, and agentcube-sdk dependencies\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10: PCAP Analyzer Sandbox Integration\n\n- [ ] **T090** Implement `SandboxRunner` class with upload_file, upload_bytes, run, and stop methods\n- [ ] **T091** Integrate SandboxRunner with PCAP analysis workflow\n\n---\n\n## Phase 11: PCAP Analyzer Container\n\n- [ ] **T100** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` with uv base image, Python 3.12, port 8000 exposure\n- [ ] **T101** Configure Dockerfile to vendor agentcube SDK\n- [ ] **T102** Verify `docker build -f example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile -t pcap-analyzer:test .` succeeds\n\n---\n\n## Phase 12: PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n\n- [ ] **T110** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` with Deployment manifest\n- [ ] **T111** Configure resource requests (cpu: 200m, memory: 100Mi) and limits (cpu: 1, memory: 1Gi)\n- [ ] **T112** Wire environment variables and secrets from pcap-analyzer-secrets\n\n---\n\n## Phase 13: PCAP Analyzer Documentation\n\n- [ ] **T120** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` with analyzer documentation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 14: Integration Verification\n\n- [ ] **T130** Verify Dify plugin structure matches requirements (AR-036-001)\n- [ ] **T131** Verify manifest.yaml contains all required fields (AR-036-002)\n- [ ] **T132** Verify tool provider and tool descriptors are correctly wired (AR-036-003, AR-036-004)\n- [ ] **T133** Verify PCAP analyzer validates API key at startup (AR-036-008-B)\n- [ ] **T134** Verify PCAP analyzer `/analyze` endpoint functionality (AR-036-008-C, AR-036-008-D)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```\nPhase 1 (T001-T005) → Phase 2 (T010-T011) → Phase 3-7 (T020-T062)\nPhase 8-10 (T070-T091) can parallel after Phase 1\nPhase 11 (T100-T102) depends on Phase 8-10\nPhase 12 (T110-T112) depends on Phase 11\nPhase 13 (T120) depends on Phase 8\nPhase 14 (T130-T134) depends on Phases 1-13\n```\n\n**Parallel:** Phases 8-10 (PCAP Analyzer core) can be done in parallel with Phases 3-7 (Dify plugin components)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Plugin package contains all required files (main.py, manifest.yaml, provider files, tool files, requirements.txt)\n- [ ] AC002: Plugin entry point executes `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n- [ ] AC003: manifest.yaml contains all required Dify plugin metadata fields\n- [ ] AC004: Provider descriptor (`provider/agentcube.yaml`) contains identity, tools list, and Python source reference\n- [ ] AC005: Tool descriptor (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`) contains complete parameter schema\n- [ ] AC006: Provider implementation raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on invalid credentials\n- [ ] AC007: Tool implementation delegates to `CodeInterpreterClient` and returns JSON messages\n- [ ] AC008: requirements.txt pins `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n- [ ] AC009: PCAP analyzer validates API key at startup and fails if missing\n- [ ] AC010: PCAP analyzer `/analyze` endpoint accepts file upload or path parameter\n- [ ] AC011: PCAP analyzer uses default configuration values when env vars are not set\n- [ ] AC012: SandboxRunner provides upload_file, upload_bytes, run, and stop methods\n- [ ] AC013: Dockerfile uses uv base image, exposes port 8000, runs pcap_analyzer.py\n- [ ] AC014: Kubernetes deployment wires secrets and environment variables correctly\n- [ ] AC015: SDK exceptions (CommandExecutionError) are properly handled\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n```bash\n# Plugin structure verification\nls -la integrations/dify-plugin/\nls -la integrations/dify-plugin/provider/\nls -la integrations/dify-plugin/tools/\n\n# PCAP analyzer build\ndocker build -f example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile -t pcap-analyzer:test .\n\n# PCAP analyzer run\ndocker run -p 8000:8000 \\\n  -e OPENAI_API_KEY=$OPENAI_API_KEY \\\n  -e ROUTER_URL=http://router:8080 \\\n  -e WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://workload-manager:8080 \\\n  pcap-analyzer:test\n\n# Test analyze endpoint (with file)\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/analyze \\\n  -F \"pcap_file=@capture.pcap\"\n\n# Test analyze endpoint (with path)\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/analyze \\\n  -F \"pcap_path=/data/capture.pcap\"\n```","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775879083892,"end":1775879083902}}}}
